Introduction: High blood pressure (hypertension) is a leading risk factor for heart diseases such as stroke and heart attack. Often asymptomatic, it is known as 'The Silent Killer'. Managing hypertension involves optimizing nitric oxide levels and reducing stress.
Risk Factors: Smoking, Alcohol Consumption, Obesity, Poor Diet (High sodium, saturated fat), Chronic Kidney Dysfunction, Hormone Imbalances, Chronic Stress, Aging, Race (higher risk in Black individuals).
Blood Pressure Classification: Normal BP: <120/<80, Elevated BP: 120-129/<80, Stage 1 Hypertension: 130-139/80-89, Stage 2 Hypertension: ≥140/≥90, Hypertensive Crisis: >180/>120.
Nitric Oxide & Blood Pressure: Nitric oxide plays a key role in vasodilation, which improves blood flow and blood pressure regulation. It is produced from L-arginine and L-citrulline, and starts in the mouth via the oral microbiome.
Lifestyle Recommendations: Quit Smoking, Avoid Antiseptic Mouthwash, Practice Nose Breathing, Manage Stress (Walking, Deep Breathing), Exercise Daily, Increase Plant-Based Foods (Beets, Garlic, Leafy Greens).
Nutrient Recommendations: Omega-3 Fatty Acids (1-4g/day), L-Citrulline (3-6g/day), Hibiscus, Lemon Verbena, Green Coffee Bean, Fucoidan, Magnesium.

Introduction: Polycystic Ovary Syndrome (PCOS) is a hormonal disorder where the ovaries produce an abnormal amount of androgens. It affects menstrual cycles and fertility. Insulin resistance is a major trigger, and lifestyle changes can help manage it.
Risk Factors: Chronic Stress, Poor Diet, Genetic Factors, High Sugar Intake, Environmental Toxins, Obesity.
Lifestyle Recommendations: Limit Toxins (Avoid BPA, PFAs, Phthalates), Balanced Diet (High Protein, High Fiber, Low Sugar), Sleep (7-8 hours), Regular Exercise (30-60 min/day).
Nutrient Recommendations: Vitamin D (5,000 IU/day), Melatonin (2 mg/day), Turmeric (1-2 g/day), Berberine (1 g/day), Omega-3 Fatty Acids (1-4 g/day).
Signs & Symptoms: Irregular periods, Hair thinning, Excess body hair, Acne, Infertility, Low-grade inflammation, Fatigue.
Insulin Resistance & PCOS: Insulin resistance causes glucose to stay in the blood instead of being used as fuel. This leads to high insulin levels, triggering excess testosterone production, inflammation, and ovarian cysts.

Introduction: Atherosclerosis, or hardening of the arteries, is an inflammatory-associated condition and the primary cause of cardiovascular disease. Modifiable lifestyle factors, such as stress, smoking, diet, exercise, and toxic burden, affect the inflammatory burden and the speed at which atherosclerosis progresses. Supporting the health of the delicate endothelial layer of the arterial wall, or the glycocalyx, is key to reducing arterial inflammation, improving vascular circulation and helping to lower cardiovascular disease risk.
Risk Factors: Smoking; Sedentary lifestyle; Chronic stress; Genetic factors; Poor diet: High sodium and saturated fat; High blood pressure; Blood sugar dysregulation
Lifestyle Recommendations: Daily Physical Activity: Continuous movement throughout the day, >20-minute, moderate- to high-intensity exercise sessions at least three to five days per week; Plant-Based Mediterranean Diet: Limit sugar, Colorful, diverse fruits and vegetables daily, Lean protein, Manage portion size; Stress Management: Commit to a plan, Practice deep breathing and meditation, Practice good sleep habits, Take at least one 10-minute walk each day; Environmental Factors: Avoid harsh cleaners and detergents, Practice good hygiene, Choose organic food whenever possible, Use a HEPA air filter at home
Nutrient Recommendations: Omega-3 Fatty Acids: Helps reduce blood pressure, triglycerides and inflammation that drive atherosclerosis; Bergamot: Significantly reduces cholesterol levels and improves cholesterol profile (total, LDL, HDL and triglycerides); also reduces fat accumulation in the liver and helps with lipid clearance; Coenzyme Q10: A critical coenzyme for energy production and cardiac function that is depleted by statin medications; Fucoidan: Bioactive compounds that help to preserve, protect and regenerate the protective layer of the blood vessel from high blood pressure and high cholesterol.
Signs & Symptoms: Blood sugar dysregulation; High blood pressure; Oxidative stress; Inflammation (ESR, hsCRP); Uric acid

Introduction: Dysautonomia is a disorder where the autonomic nervous system (ANS) malfunctions, affecting functions like heart rate, blood pressure, digestion, and temperature control. It often involves an imbalance between the parasympathetic (rest-and-digest) and sympathetic (fight-or-flight) systems.
Lifestyle Recommendations: Increase Dietary Fiber, Increase Salt & Water Intake, Improve Vagal Tone (Humming, Singing, Meditation, Cold Water Therapy), Eat Frequent Small Meals, Personalized Movement Plan.
Nutrient Recommendations: Omega-3 Fatty Acids (1-4g/day), Phosphatidylcholine (5-10g/day), Mitochondrial Support (NAC: 600mg, ALC: 500mg, ALA: 200mg, GSH: 500mg), Vascular Support (Diosmin: 600mg, Troxerutin: 500mg, Gotu Kola: 200mg, Horse Chestnut Extract: 300mg), Probiotics + Saccharomyces boulardii (20-450 billion CFU, 2-10 billion CFU).
Signs & Symptoms: Dizziness, Unstable blood pressure & heart rate, Digestive complaints, Fatigue, Poor circulation, Brain fog, Headaches, Blotchy skin, Tingling fingers & toes.
Causes: Severe stress, Trauma, Extreme hormone fluctuations, Stroke, Post-viral infection, Vagus nerve imbalance.
Autonomic Nervous System & Responses: The autonomic nervous system has two branches: Parasympathetic (rest and digest, anti-inflammatory) and Sympathetic (fight or flight, pro-inflammatory). Imbalance in these systems leads to various symptoms.

Description: 4sight is formulated with a specific blend of antioxidants, minerals and botanicals, all of which have been demonstrated in research to support healthy eye function.
Contents: The eye is the organ most susceptible to oxidative damage caused by light, toxins (smoke), and atmospheric oxygen. The formula includes potent antioxidants and key nutrients to protect the eyes from free radical damage and maintain the long-term health of the eyes. Lipoic acid, a potent, versatile antioxidant, “recharges” other vital antioxidants such as vitamins E and C and glutathione. The carotenoids lutein and zeaxanthin are found in high concentrations in the macula lutea portion of the eye. These strong antioxidants have been shown to protect the lens protein, lipid membranes, and DNA from oxidative damage to help improve visual acuity. Zinc, a vital coenzyme for eye tissue, is a necessary component in antioxidant enzymes including superoxide dismutase, glutathione peroxidase and catalase. Zinc also stimulates the enzymes responsible for digesting rod outer segments and preventing the build-up of lipofuscin, a lipid-containing residue caused by normal “wear and tear” that can impair vision

Description: Formulated for those who are “stressed and tired,” Adapten-All® includes a blend of key micronutrients and adaptogenic botanicals formulated to strengthen the body’s stress response and support healthy energy levels
Contents: Extended periods of stress not only burden the stress response system, but can also result in mental and physical fatigue, nervousness, irritability and poor memory. Rhodiola rosea root extract is categorized as an adaptogenic botanical due to its ability to increase resistance to variety of stressors. Within the central nervous system, Rhodiola has been shown to preserve levels of neurotransmitters such as serotonin, dopamine and norepinephrine. Eleuthero root extract is a strong adaptogenic botanical widely used in China to support general health, memory and endurance. In addition to improving stress resilience and fighting fatigue, Eleuthero has exhibited immune supporting effects. Schisandra berry extract is a botanical used for centuries in China and Russia to help support mental clarity, stress response and emotional health. Licorice root extract promotes healthy cortisol levels by inhibiting an enzyme that converts cortisol to its inactive form, cortisone. This is important for individuals who need support for maintaining healthy inflammatory balance. Ashwagandha root extract is a botanical that helps calm the nervous system and supports sleep cycle regulation and healthy thyroid function

Description:
Bergamot BPF is clinically proven to dramatically affect
 multiple biomarkers associated with cardiometabolic health.
Contents: Optimizing cardiometabolic wellness begins with maintaining healthy cholesterol levels already within the normal range and normal inflammatory balance. Circulating cholesterol levels are primarily controlled by the liver, specifically the rate-limiting enzyme HMG-CoA reductase. Because of its cholesterol-balancing role, HMG-CoA reductase is a target of many traditional therapies, but studies indicate these therapies deplete the metabolic reserve of several critical nutrients and do not provide an antioxidant benefit.

Description: Bergamot BPF maintains normal inflammatory balance, glucose regulation, arterial health, healthy cholesterol levels already within the normal range and cardiometabolic wellness.
Contents: Optimizing cardiovascular health is a leading concern for many adults, and maintaining balanced cholesterol levels is an important part of that process. Though cholesterol can be consumed through food, circulating cholesterol levels are primarily produced and controlled by the liver using the rate control enzyme, HMG-CoA reductase (HMGCR). Because of its pronounced role in cholesterol synthesis, inhibiting HMGCR has become a primary target of many traditional therapies. Bergamot (Citrus bergamia) is a citrus plant that grows almost exclusively in the narrow coastal Calabria region in southern Italy. The local population quickly discovered bergamot juice could be used to help support healthy cholesterol levels and optimize cardiovascular wellness. Bergamot BPF’s health benefits derive from its unique profile of phenolic compounds such as neoeriocitrin, neohesperidin and naringin. Naringin has been shown to be beneficial in maintaining healthy inflammatory balance while neoeriocitrin has been found to exhibit a strong capacity to quench free radicals and maintain healthy LDL cholesterol levels. Also, bergamot naturally contains large amounts of brutieridin and melitidin, which have a unique ability to dampen HMG-CoA reductase.

Description: Betaine & Pepsin includes two essential components of healthy digestion: hydrochloric acid and the digestive enzyme pepsin.
Contents: An estimated 30% of Americans suffer from low levels of acidity, which can result in the incomplete digestion of foods and displacement of food in the stomach. Hydrochloric acid (HCl) is vital in the proper digestion of proteins and the absorption of minerals like vitamin B12 and calcium. It also plays an important role in signaling the pancreas to release digestive enzymes. Pepsin is one of the first enzymes to initiate protein digestion and works in synergy with HCl to provide complete digestive support.
FORMULATION ADVANTAGE:: While many competitor products are available in tablet form, Betaine & Pepsin is encapsulated for quick release in the stomach to enhance digestive benefits.

Contents: Phospholipids are an integral part of biological membranes, and they tend to decrease as we age. They are critical for cell and mitochondrial membrane shape, repair and growth. Proper cell membrane function facilitates healthy cell signaling, which is important for energy production, immune function and regulating inflammatory cascades. BioPC Pro® leverages the benefits of a full-spectrum blend of phosphatides, including phosphatidylcholine, phosphatidylethanolamine, phosphatidylinositol and phosphatidylserine, to bolster parasympathetic tone in patients who may be sympathetic-dominant. These phosphatides help achieve nervous system balance and provide a vital choline source to help optimize acetylcholine levels, which can be compromised in sympathetic dominance. In addition, BioPC Pro® helps process fats and supports better focus, brain health, and cognitive function. This high-concentration phosphatide blend is naturally bioavailable and rapidly absorbed. Adding BioPC Pro® to a smoothie creates a creamy texture and is an easy way to get all the benefits of a full-spectrum phosphatide blend!

Contents: Created from multiple vitamin C-rich sources, C-Flav provides antioxidant protection, enhances immune function and supports healthy collagen synthesis and connective tissue. C-Flav also helps maintain normal inflammatory balance throughout the body. Humans lack the enzyme required to synthesize vitamin C and, therefore, must obtain the vitamin from their diets. Description: Candicid Forte includes a comprehensive blend of nutrients, fatty acids, and botanicals to promote healthy microbial balance, enhance immune function, and soothe the gastrointestinal lining
Contents: More than 70% of the body’s immune system resides in the gut, so establishing a healthy microbial balance is critical for reducing immune challenges and maintaining healthy inflammatory balance. Biotin helps to establish microbial balance by preventing yeast, especially Candida albicans, from converting to its more invasive fungal form. In addition, sodium caprylate is included to disrupt the metabolism of Candida and create a hostile environment for colonization. Description: Cardio B includes targeted amounts of folic acid, B12, B6 and betaine (trimethylglycine) to aggressively support methylation pathways in the body.
Contents: Methylation is a vitamin-requiring biochemical process in the body critical for maintaining mental and physical health. Methylation helps convert the problematic amino acid metabolite homocysteine into the amino acids methionine and cysteine. Consistent recycling of homocysteine is vital for supporting cardiovascular health. Proper methylation can be inhibited by nutrient deficiencies in folic acid, B6 and B12. Certain medications such as acetaminophen, aspirin, ibuprofen and oral contraceptives can also deplete blood levels of these crucial B vitamins, reducing the body’s vital methylation capacity. Adequate levels of folic acid and vitamin B12 are considered two of the most important nutrients required to balance homocysteine levels. They work together in several processes, including synthesis of DNA and red blood cells, and the maintenance of the myelin sheath surrounding nerve cells. Vitamin B6 works with folic acid and vitamin B12 in the recycling of homocysteine. Betaine (trimethylglycine) contributes to the recycling process, and also functions in the body as a methyl donor. Cardio B specifically targets homocysteine recycling for optimal cardiovascular and arterial health.

Description: Cardio MET Pack® provides a complete protocol for cardiometabolic health, containing a trio of scientifically validated formulas in convenient, easy-to-take packets.
Contents: Supporting cardiometabolic health often requires a multifaceted approach, including blood sugar balance, inflammatory balance and cholesterol support. Cardio MET Pack® simplifies this by making it easy to take these three foundational, comprehensive formulas in convenient packets. Each packet contains CM Core®, a powerful combination of berberine and alpha lipoic acid (ALA), which helps maintain heart function, metabolism, antioxidant status, and lipid and glucose levels already within the normal range. Orthomega® 820 is also included, and contains 430 mg of eicosapentaenoic acid (EPA) and 390 mg of docosahexaenoic acid (DHA) omega-3 fatty acids per soft gel. In addition, 50 mg of docosapentaenoic acid (DPA) acts a reserve for EPA and DHA. EPA, DHA and DPA are provided as triglycerides, the preferred form for superior absorption. Finally, Bergamot BPF is included and provides a powerful and unique array of cardio-protective polyphenolic flavonoids that help maintain healthy cholesterol levels already within the normal range.

Description: CDG EstroDIM® is a targeted supplement that combines the synergistic benefits of the cruciferous vegetable metabolites indole-3-carbinol (I3C) and diindolylmethane (DIM), plus calcium D-glucarate, to support estrogen metabolism and breast and prostate health.
Contents: Estrogen collectively refers to female hormones that carry chemical messages to cells throughout the body. The hormones deliver the important message of “grow, divide and multiply.” It is for this reason that hormones are vital in human development and tissue repair. Supporting proper estrogen synthesis, metabolism and detoxification is essential for proper hormonal balance. I3C helps achieve this goal through its ability to temper estrogen signals by competing for binding sites and inhibiting the activity of estrogen receptors. The second phytonutrient compound, DIM, promotes beneficial estrogen metabolism in both sexes and enhances the potential for greater antioxidant activity. Calcium D-glucarate is the supplemental calcium salt form of D-glucaric acid, a substance found naturally in the body and in consumption of certain fruits and vegetables. Calcium D-glucarate has been extensively studied and shown to inhibit beta-glucaronidase, an enzyme found in certain gut bacteria. This activity supports the body’s ability to detoxify estrogens, foreign molecules and fat-soluble toxins.

Description: Cerenity® is designed to address daily stress by increasing production of the neurotransmitters serotonin and gamma aminobutyric acid (GABA) in the brain.
Contents: Neurotransmitters are the chemical messengers that regulate mood, memory, sleep cycle and daily stress. High levels of stress, dietary deficiencies, genetics, medications and toxins all play a role in neurotransmitter depletion. The nutrients in Cerenity® support healthy neurotransmitter levels for balancing the stress response. L-theanine, an amino acid found in green tea, has been shown to quickly improve stress perception and resilience. PharmaGABA™, a patented and naturally sourced form of GABA, has been shown to promote relaxation in the central nervous system. 5-hydroxytryptophan (5-HTP) is an amino acid intermediate that is directly converted into the mood-regulating neurotransmitter serotonin. Taurine is an amino acid that activates GABA receptors. Inositol is crucial for the release of neurotransmitters from within nerve cells. The essential micronutrients included in Cerenity® aid in the synthesis of serotonin and GABA. The support of these neurotransmitters helps promote a relaxed mental state, positive outlook and restful sleep cycle.

Description: Cerenity® PM is a comprehensive neurotransmitter formula designed to help with occasional sleeplessness. It helps patients fall asleep faster, stay asleep longer, and reach deeper, restorative stages of sleep.
Contents: Sleep is the body’s way of metabolically and psychologically resetting itself. In order to maintain restorative sleep, the brain must have optimal levels of serotonin and gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA), the relaxing and sleep-regulating neurotransmitters, as well as the sleep-regulating hormone, melatonin. The synergistic ingredients in Cerenity® PM promote relaxation prior to bedtime and promote deep, restorative stages of sleep. The formula includes GABA in the form of PharmaGABA™, a patented, naturally sourced form of GABA shown to promote relaxation in the nervous system. Another ingredient, 5-hydroxytryptophan (5-HTP), has been shown in clinical studies to promote and enhance sleep, especially REM sleep. Phosphatidylserine is also included to address elevated evening cortisol levels that may contribute to frequent waking.

Description: CereVive is formulated to support a positive mental outlook and a relaxed, focused state.
Contents: CereVive includes amino acid precursors and bioactive nutrients that support healthy levels of neurotransmitters like gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA), serotonin, dopamine, norepinephrine and epinephrine. L-theanine, an amino acid found in green tea, has been shown to quickly improve stress perception and resilience. PharmaGABA™, a patented and naturally sourced form of GABA, has been shown to promote relaxation in the central nervous system. Mucuna pruriens extract, commonly known as velvet bean, includes standardized doses of L-dopa. L-dopa is the direct precursor to the neurotransmitter dopamine, which helps maintain a positive outlook and cognitive function. Maintaining adequate neurotransmitter production is vital for regulating mood, appetite, memory, energy levels and sleep cycle. High levels of stress, dietary deficiencies, genetics, medications and toxins all play a role in neurotransmitter depletion. CereVive provides the nutrients required to help optimize neurotransmitter production and maintain overall wellness.

Description: Chondro-Flx combines glucosamine sulfate, chondroitin sulfate, vitamin C and bromelain, all of which have been shown in research to support joint health.
Contents:
Lifestyle factors and age can contribute to a breakdown of healthy cartilage and 
lead to nutrient and fluid deprivation in the affected articular cartilage. Most post
exercise therapies simply block the pain of joint discomfort, and in doing so inhibit the 
regeneration and elongation of chondroitin sulfate polymers that maintain joint health.  
As key precursors to cartilage formation, the ingredients in Chondro-Flx provide 
full support for joint integrity and movement and a normal inflammatory response. 
Glucosamine sulfate is a naturally occurring, joint-supporting compound and is the 
starting point for cartilage synthesis. Chondroitin sulfate is associated with articular 
cartilage and is designed to draw water into the joint tissue to provide hydration, 
allowing for the management of pressure put on the joints. Bromelain, a protease 
derived from pineapple stems, affects both the kinin and fibrin pathways helping to 
maintain inflammatory balance, and increases the absorption of chondroitin sulfate. 
The formula also includes vitamin C, an antioxidant that reduces free radicals and acts 
as a cofactor to enzymes critical for the synthesis of new collagen.
FORMULATION ADVANTAGE:: While most chondroitin sulfate available on the market is acid-hydrolyzed, a process that makes the molecules too large to be absorbed, the chondroitin sulfate used in Chondro-Flx is enzymatically processed to provide consistently small, highly absorbed chondroitin molecules and ensure optimal results.

Description: CitraNOX® is a unique formula designed to maintain healthy blood pressure levels already within the normal range by enhancing nitric oxide synthesis.
Contents: The aging process, an overconsumption of high glycemic load foods, stress, physical inactivity and toxic burden can all wreak havoc on endothelial cells by disrupting inflammatory balance. This disruption can lead to arterial rigidity and vasoconstriction, due to a decrease in circulating nitric oxide (NO) levels. NO is a potent vasodilator and cell signaling molecule. NO is produced with the help of endothelial nitric oxide synthase (eNOS) during the recycling of L-arginine to L-citrulline in the urea cycle. NO diffuses into the smooth muscle cells lining arteries and initiates a cascade of phosphorylation reactions resulting in smooth muscle relaxation and vasodilation of the artery. Using a combination of high-dose L-citrulline, quercetin and grape seed extract, CitraNOX® delivers full-spectrum support to help maintain healthy inflammatory balance, arterial elasticity, optimal nitric oxide levels and blood flow. Recent research shows that when compared to L-arginine, supplemental L-citrulline maintains peak plasma NO levels for twice the length of time, resulting in normal blood flow. Quercetin is a well-known flavonoid shown to inhibit ICAM-1 and NFkB, allowing for a normal inflammatory balance. A study completed on 27 volunteers showed that MegaNatural® BP, a premium grape seed extract, was found to maintain healthy blood pressure levels after four weeks of supplementation.

Description:
CM Core®, a formula backed by extensive clinical 
research, is designed to address several factors 
associated with ideal cardiometabolic health.
Contents:
CM Core® provides a powerful formula for those seeking to optimize the multiple 
mechanisms of cardiovascular and metabolic health. The powerful combination of 
berberine and alpha lipoic acid (ALA) helps maintain heart function, metabolism, 
antioxidant status, and lipid and glucose levels already within the normal range. 
Among their numerous benefits, berberine and ALA activate the master metabolic 
switch, adenosine mono-phosphate kinase (AMPK). Activation of this powerful 
metabolic enzyme triggers a variety of genes that help improve metabolism, stabilize 
mitochondria, and enhance insulin sensitivity. Clinical trials demonstrate that berberine 
administration supports cardiometabolic health by maintaining healthy glucose levels, 
supporting normal LDL levels and optimizing metabolism. ALA is a well-known, potent 
antioxidant that scavenges free radicals and helps regenerate vitamin C, vitamin E and 
glutathione. Several studies have demonstrated that ALA supports normal glucose 
levels as well as maintains healthy blood vessel and circulatory health.

Description:
CollaGEN combines type I hydrolyzed collagen, type II bioactive collagen peptides, 
mucopolysaccharides, and essential cofactors magnesium and vitamin C to protect and  
preserve connective tissue synthesis and regeneration.
Contents:
Collagen is the primary structural protein found in connective tissue—it gives tendons, ligaments, fascia, cartilage, bone and skin structural stability. During collagen synthesis, amino acids are 
combined to form polypeptide chains. These chains are dependent on the cofactors magnesium and vitamin C to form the collagen triple helix. Lack of raw materials and essential 
cofactors, in addition to an unhealthy lifestyle, can lead to a weakened collagen structure. Over time, tissue elasticity and cellular production of type I and II collagen and hyaluronic acid 
decreases. Simultaneously, mechanical stress, cytokines and reactive oxygen species disrupt the process of collagen biosynthesis, resulting in weaker fibers.

Description:
Collagen Factors provides key nutrients proven to support healthy connective 
tissue in the skin, tendons, ligaments, cartilage, joints and bone
Contents:
Collagen Factors provides Mobilee®, a patented hyaluronic acid concentrate 
clinically proven to stimulate the body's own synthesis of hyaluronic acid, support 
muscle strength, and decrease joint inflammatory mediators to help support normal 
joint function and mobility. Vitamin C, L-proline and L-lysine help maintain 
all connective tissue structure and biomechanical properties by creating pro
collagen and stimulating collagen biosynthesis. L-proline is a major amino acid that 
is important for maintaining youthful skin, joints and tendons, and it is an essential 
component of collagen. L-lysine supports the collagen matrix that contributes to 
bone cartilage, connective tissue, veins, arteries and capillaries. Vitamin C—along with 
the amino acids proline and lysine—is essential for healthy collagen formation.  Zinc 
plays an important role in the structure of proteins and cell membranes. MSM helps 
maintain disulfide bonds that keep collagen strands strong and preserves connective 
tissue pliancy, which is crucial for supporting healthy joints, tendons, ligaments 
and other connective tissue. MSM has been shown to increase plasma glutathione, 
activating collagen’s defensive mechanisms against oxidative stress. Manganese is 
a structural component of antioxidant enzymes, facilitates bone development, and 
helps make amino acids

Description:
CopaCalm® is formulated to address daily stress 
and provide a state of relaxed focus without 
drowsiness.  This is especially beneficial at the 
time of a stressful occurrence or in anticipation of 
a stressful event
Contents:
CopaCalm® contains a combination of ingredients designed to address stressful 
situations in the moment or may be taken in preparation for these events.  
L-theanine, an amino acid found in green tea, has been shown to quickly improve 
stress perception and resilience. GABA is the primary inhibitory neurotransmitter 
in the brain.  It has been shown to prevent stress-related messages and promote 
relaxation in the central nervous system. Huperzine alkaloids are derived from 
Huperzia serrata (whole plant extract), or Chinese club moss.  As a potent and selective 
acetylcholinesterase inhibitor, huperzine A helps to improve memory and support 
optimal cognitive health.

Description:
Coenzyme Q10
 (CoQ10
 ), also known as ubiquinone, is a 
pro-enzyme produced naturally within the body. CoQ10
 
plays a critical role in energy (ATP) production and is 
one of the most powerful lipid-soluble antioxidants
Contents:
CoQ10
 is a potent antioxidant that prevents lipid and mitochondrial DNA oxidation. 
The body’s ability to produce and metabolize CoQ10
 has been reported to decrease 
with age. CoQ10
 deficiency may also be caused by impairment in CoQ10
 production, 
drug-induced depletion, gene mutations or oxidative stress. CoQ-10 is delivered 
in an oil-based, proprietary formulation and includes vitamin E for enhanced 
absorption and maximum stability

Contents:

 is a potent antioxidant that prevents lipid and mitochondrial DNA oxidation.

is an essential component of cellular energy production and has been shown to

300 mg is highly concentrated for those that need to quickly and effectively increase

 .  It is delivered in an oil-based, proprietary formulation and includes

The Core Restore® kit includes three active formulas—Core Support, MitoCORE® and PhytoCore— which function synergistically to provide the energy and nutritional cofactors for active biotransformation.
Contents:
These formulas support both Phase I and Phase II pathways of liver biotransformation while promoting Phase III elimination pathways.
 How Core Restore® 
Helps Your Body Detoxify

 Core Restore® is a comprehensive program that removes toxins,

GENTLE

 In addition, the standard American diet, which is high in sugar and caffeine while low in nutrient density and fiber, has been shown to slow detoxification

Description:
Cosmedix includes an array of essential vitamins, minerals and 
phytonutrients needed to support healthy skin, hair and nails.
Contents:
Research shows collagen production begins to decrease at around age 18 and 
continues to decline at a rate of about 1% each year after age 40. After menopause, 
skin thickness may decrease at a rate of about 1.13% annually. Betaine HCl supports 
optimal protein breakdown, allowing for more efficient manufacturing of collagen 
during years of decreased collagen production. MSM is a source of bioavailable 
sulfur, which plays an integral role in regeneration of collagen in skin and hair. Saw 
palmetto is added to support normal levels of dihydrotestosterone (DHT), known to 
promote the health and thickness of hair. This formulation also includes key nutrients 
such as silica (from horsetail grass), biotin and vitamin A to provide a complete 
spectrum of support for healthy skin, hair and nails.

Description:
Cryptolepis is a plant containing alkaloids, tannins 
and flavones that helps maintain microbial balance.
Contents:
Cryptolepis sanguinolenta is a plant that is traditionally used in Ghana and other 
regions of Africa for addressing various microbial challenges. It helps maintain 
normal inflammatory and microbial balance, and provides antioxidant support 
for those with high spirochete load. Spirochetes are bacteria that are usually 
spread by tick bites, and are often accompanied by other associated microbes 
that can make recovery especially challenging. Cryptolepis and its main alkaloid, 
cryptolepine, have shown microbial balancing activity for inhibiting unwanted 
bacterial organisms, including strong activity against both growing and non
growing stationary phase spirochetes. Cryptolepis tincture is often used alongside 
other plants such as cat’s claw, Japanese knotweed, Andrographis, and sweet 
wormwood for a comprehensive approach to maintaining microbial balance and 
reducing immune burden.

Description:
Cystistatin is a botanical blend formulated to 
promote a healthy urinary tract.
Contents:
The botanical formula in Cystistatin promotes microbial balance and supports 
immune function for a healthy urinary tract. Bacteria can enter the urinary tract 
through the urethra or, in rare cases, the bloodstream. Women are generally at 
greater risk for this occurrence. One of the key ingredients in Cystistatin is uva ursi 
leaf extract, standardized to include the microbial-balancing compound arbutin. 
The dried leaves of uva ursi not only provide arbutin, but also methylarbutin, 
flavonoids, allantoin, tannins, gallic and ellagic acids, volatile oils and urvone. These 
components work synergistically to promote healthy bacterial balance in the 
urinary tract. Another primary ingredient, berberine hydrochloride, is extracted 
from the roots and barks of many plants. It is effective in blocking the adhesion of 
microbes to host cells. The botanicals marshmallow root, celery seed extract 
and bladderwrack leaf are also important for microbial balance in the urinary 
system. The soothing activity of marshmallow root results in the promotion of a 
healthy mucosal surface in the urinary tissues and membranes. Celery seed extract 
and bladderwrack are supported by research to promote a healthy flushing of the 
urinary tract.

Description:
D-Hist Jr.™ is a great-tasting, chewable tablet 
that includes a targeted blend of flavonoids, 
antioxidants, proteolytic enzymes and botanicals.
Contents:
D-Hist Jr.™ is designed to provide comprehensive support for children with seasonal 
challenges caused by common environmental allergens. The unique nutritional 
combination safely promotes healthy mucosal passages for children with elevated 
histamine and respiratory irritation. Quercetin is known for its ability to stabilize 
mast cells, thereby diminishing the release of histamine, the compound known to 
cause hypersensitivity reactions. Studies have shown stinging nettle leaf (Urtica 
dioica) balances immune and inflammatory responses, specifically in the airways 
and nasal passages. Bromelain is a plant enzyme naturally found in pineapples 
and has been shown to enhance the absorption of quercetin. Bromelain has also 
been shown to reduce circulating allergenic protein complexes associated with 
hyperimmune sensitivity and seasonal discomfort. N-acetyl cysteine (NAC) is 
an amino acid precursor to one of the most important antioxidants in the body, 
glutathione. Both glutathione and NAC help reduce the viscosity of mucus, 
allowing for cleared airways and improved respiratory health. Vitamin C cannot 
be synthesized by humans and is therefore an essential nutrient that must be 
consumed in the diet. Among its numerous health-promoting properties, vitamin 
C is distinctively beneficial for individuals with seasonal discomfort because of its 
ability to deactivate histamine. It supports the immune system and also acts as a 
potent antioxidant.

Description:
DG Protect is a uniquely designed digestive enzyme targeting gluten and 
dairy digestion.
Contents:
Patients with gluten and dairy sensitivities require protection and flexibility in food 
choices. The unique enzyme blend in DG Protect helps digest both gluten and 
dairy proteins and lactose to ensure each food component is effectively broken 
down for better absorption and a controlled immune response. DG Protect includes 
endopeptidase and exopeptidase activity to break down gluten proteins, as well 
as a unique mixture of protease enzymes and lactase to support digestion of 
multiple constituents of milk and dairy products.

Description:
DGL, or deglycyrrhizinated licorice, is a form of licorice root that has been 
specially processed to include only biologically active flavonoids.
Contents:
DGL, or deglycyrrhizinated licorice, is a form of licorice root that has been specially 
processed to contain only biologically active flavonoids, without glycyrrhizin. The 
deglycyrrhized form of licorice allows for higher dosing of supportive flavonoids, 
which helps maintain a healthy mucosal surface in the stomach. Traditionally used to 
support GI-related complaints, research has shown DGL promotes bacterial balance 
and a healthy esophageal lining. Along with DGL, the formula also contains aloe vera, 
slippery elm bark and marshmallow root, all used to soothe the GI tract. Each 
serving contains 150 mg DGL. Since almost 80% of pathogens enter the body through 
either mucosal tissue or remain localized on mucosal surfaces, a healthy mucosal 
lining is of the utmost importance for digestive health.

Description:
DHEA, or dehydroepiandrosterone, is a  steroid hormone precursor that helps 
promote healthy hormone levels and supports the stress response system.
Contents:
DHEA is a crucial counterpart to the stress hormone cortisol. It maintains normal 
inflammatory balance and protects brain tissues, such as the hippocampus, where 
excessive cortisol secretion can affect mood regulation and memory. Because of the 
catabolic effect excessive cortisol levels have on the body, balancing the cortisol
to-DHEA ratio has been shown to reverse classic stress-induced physiological 
responses, promote optimal bone density and support healthy aging. DHEA 
supplementation is particularly important for those that have been found to be 
deficient through testing, as well as those who need immediate cortisol-to-DHEA 
ratio support. This formulation includes either 5 mg or 25 mg of DHEA derived 
from wild yam, allowing for incremental oral supplementation and flexibility with 
numerous hormone-balancing and stress-fighting protocols.

Description:
Diaxinol® is a natural and synergistic formula for 
promoting balanced blood sugar levels.
Contents:
Through enhanced signaling at the cellular level, this blend of natural extracts and 
vitamins supports healthy blood glucose levels by repairing the insulin-sensitizing 
pathway. The unique and effective formulation contains five ingredients provided at 
targeted doses for maximum efficacy. In addition to its well-known, potent antioxidant 
properties, alpha lipoic acid (ALA) has been shown to support healthy blood sugar 
balance by activating the master metabolic switch adenosine mono-phosphate kinase 
(AMPK). AMPK activates cellular metabolism by improving insulin sensitivity, down
regulating genes involved in fat storage and activating genes involved with burning 
fat. Diaxinol® also includes Cinnulin® (cinnamon bark extract), which has a beneficial 
effect on blood sugar levels, first by inhibiting the enzymes that cause insulin resistance 
and second, by increasing insulin sensitivity. A third ingredient, chromium, is critical in 
the uptake of glucose into cells because it is a valuable piece in the molecule glucose 
tolerance factor (GTF). Several studies have demonstrated a significant improvement in 
markers of blood sugar balance, insulin sensitivity and blood fats when supplementing 
with chromium. In a similar way, biotin helps maintain healthy blood sugar balance by 
stimulating glucose-induced insulin secretion and accelerating glucose metabolism in 
the liver and pancreas. Vanadyl sulfate (VS) is the stable, inorganic form of vanadium, a 
mineral shown to mimic the action of insulin. VS plays a major role in promoting healthy 
glucose uptake by stimulating AKT, a potent activator of the glucose transport, GLUT4.

Description:
Digestzyme-V is an extensive blend of acid
resistant, plant-based enzymes designed to 
help maximize the digestion and absorption of 
nutrients from food.
Contents:
Each capsule includes lipase, amylase, lactase, protease and CereCalase® to aid 
in the breakdown of protein, fat, starches, fiber and other difficult-to-digest foods. 
Poor digestion can cause occasional bloating and gas, cramping, and constipation, 
among other gastrointestinal issues. Conversely, proper digestion of food prevents 
fermentation in the gut and the proliferation of “bad” bacteria at the expense of 
“good” intestinal bacteria. Digestzyme-V is designed to support digestion and 
absorption of nutrients by using plant-based enzymes, rather than the traditional 
animal-based enzymes. Plant-based enzymes can function in a wider pH range of 
2.5–8.5, as compared to the 6.5–7.5 necessary to activate animal-based enzymes, 
and still offer the same digestive strength. This broad pH range makes Digestzyme-V 
especially beneficial for individuals with lower gastric acid levels or inconsistent pH 
levels. Each enzyme has been tested for  
pH, temperature and gastric survivability  
to ensure enzyme activity, allowing for full-spectrum digestive support.

Description:
EstroDIM® is a targeted supplement that combines the cruciferous vegetable 
metabolites indole-3-carbinol (I3C) and diindolylmethane (DIM) to support 
proper estrogen metabolism.
Contents:
The formulation of I3C and DIM together creates the ideal combination of 
metabolites to support estrogen balance and breast and prostate health. Estrogen 
collectively refers to female hormones that carry chemical messages to cells 
throughout the body. The most important message hormones deliver is, “grow, 
divide and multiply.” It is for this reason that hormones are so important in human 
development and tissue repair. Supporting proper estrogen synthesis, metabolism 
and detoxification is essential for proper hormonal balance. I3C helps achieve 
this goal through its ability to temper estrogen signals by competing for binding 
sites and inhibiting the activity of estrogen receptors. The second phytonutrient 
compound, DIM, promotes beneficial estrogen metabolism and enhances the 
potential for greater antioxidant activity. Together, I3C and DIM promote the 
creation of the more favorable and protective 2-hydroxyestrone (2-OHE) metabolite 
versus production of 4-hydroxyestrone (4-OHE) and 16-alpha-hydroxyestrone 
(16-alphaOHE) metabolites, which can overstimulate cells and create free radicals that 
cause DNA damage.
Formulated_For:
ENDOCRINE 
HEALTH
 WOMEN'S HEALTH
 MEN'S HEALTH

Description:
Femarin is a targeted blend of botanicals formulated to provide support for a 
comfortable and balanced menopausal transition.
Contents:
Femarin can provide symptomatic relief for common complaints associated with 
menopause, such as hot flashes, night sweats and frequent night waking, while 
serving as a foundation for overall wellness during this period of life. Black cohosh 
root extract has been shown to significantly reduce menopause-related symptoms, 
even when compared to other regimens in double-blind, placebo-controlled 
studies. Resveratrol, a polyphenol found in grapes and red wine, has been shown 
to have an effect on free radical scavenging and antioxidant properties in tissues. 
Similar in structure to estrogen, trans-resveratrol provides a range of supportive 
activities including hormonal balance and promoting normal inflammatory balance. 
Licorice root extract contains flavonoids, such as glabridin, which have been 
shown to exert a balancing effect on estrogen levels. In addition, licorice root extract 
has been shown to support healthy bone mineral density in postmenopausal 
women. Gamma oryzanol (ferulic acid) is a natural compound extracted from rice 
bran oil. One study in which 40 women were given a dose of 300 mg/day of gamma 
oryzanol resulted in a reduction in menopausal symptoms in 85% of the subjects. 
The dried roots of the Dong quai plant have flavonoids and essential oils that 
support female hormone balance

Description:
Fiber MGP is a next-generation fiber supplement that delivers 12 g of fiber per serving and features clinically researched ingredients that promote healthy 
microbiome modulation, GLP-1 activation, and prebiotic seeding. This unique fiber blend improves digestive regularity and gut barrier function and promotes 
metabolic health
Contents:
Fiber MGP is an innovative fiber product that promotes healthy microbiome modulation, GLP-1 (glucagon-like peptide-1) 
activation, and prebiotic seeding. Delivering a powerful 12-gram dose of fiber per serving, Fiber MGP provides a significant 
fiber payload to help patients meet their daily goals. In addition, this formula combines three clinically studied ingredients: 
Livaux® (gold kiwifruit), Solnul® (resistant potato starch), and baobab fruit powder. Livaux® is a precision prebiotic shown 
to increase levels of Faecalibacterium prausnitzii, a keystone bacterium known for its ability to reduce intestinal permeability, 
boost butyrate production, and increase GLP-1 production. Solnul® resistant potato starch further enhances gut health by 
increasing microbiome diversity and significantly increasing Akkermansia muciniphila levels—up to 238% in clinical studies—
 thereby promoting metabolic health and GLP-1 production. This increase in GLP-1 production and release plays a role in 
regulating cravings, satiety and maintaining balanced blood sugar, contributing to a more favorable metabolic profile. Baobab 
fruit powder extract provides additional fiber plus essential vitamins, minerals, polyphenols and amino acids. These nutrients 
support microbiome diversity and immune resilience and help maintain normal inflammatory balance.The slow fermentation of these key ingredients minimizes GI discomfort, making Fiber MGP ideal for patients seeking 
effective, gentle digestive support. By combining high fiber content with targeted prebiotics and nutrient-dense baobab, 
Fiber MGP offers a multimodal approach to gut health that addresses regularity, microbiome balance and metabolic benefits 
without the common side effects of fiber supplementation.
Formulated_For:
GASTROINTESTINAL 
HEALTH
 GLP-1 PRODUCTION CRAVING CONTROL BLOOD SUGAR SUPPORT
FORMULATION ADVANTAGE::
Fiber MGP delivers one of the highest fiber payloads available, combining 
superior efficacy with a smooth texture that makes daily fiber intake easy  
and pleasant!
 • This advanced fiber formula restores keystone probiotic strains F. prausnitzii 
and Akkermansia to support better GI barrier function and GLP-1 production.

Description:
Flora Bites is a delicious, chewable probiotic for 
children, designed to deliver beneficial bacteria 
and promote healthy gut flora. Ideal for children 
who prefer an alternative to powder formulas.
Contents:
The natural balance of flora in the GI tract can be disrupted by factors including poor 
dietary intake. One of the key benefits of probiotics is their ability to increase the 
population of healthy bacteria to combat microbial imbalance. Flora Bites includes 
Lactobacillus and Bifidobacterium probiotic strains, as well as 20 mg of vitamin C for 
comprehensive gastrointestinal and immune support. The chewable cube form is an 
easy, fun way for children to achieve optimal probiotic support.

Description:
FloraBoost is a probiotic formula for children, 
designed to deliver bacteria and promote 
healthy gut flora, protect intestinal integrity 
and boost immune function.
Contents:
The seven strains of beneficial bacteria, plus Saccharomyces boulardii, in 
FloraBoost have been strategically selected based on research that supports their 
survivability and adherence to the intestinal tract. FloraBoost comes in a powder 
form for easy administration to children and is especially beneficial for those with 
occasional diarrhea. The natural flora balance of the gastrointestinal tract can be 
disrupted by factors including chlorinated water and poor dietary intake. One of the 
key benefits of probiotics is their ability to increase the population of healthy bacteria 
to combat microbial imbalance. The challenge to this major health benefit lies in the 
survivability of these living organisms. The technology used in the manufacturing 
of FloraBoost ensures the long-term effectiveness of the probiotic formula. The 
microorganisms in this formula are protected and sealed, and remain dormant until 
exposed to moisture in the GI tract. Saccharomyces boulardii is a probiotic yeast that 
actively supports immune defenses by increasing levels of secretory IgA, the crucial 
antibody that helps bind and clear harmful bacteria.

Description: GABAnol is a synergistic combination of gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA), glycine and Dong quai, which serves as a quick response supplement for muscle relaxation
Contents:
GABA is the primary neurotransmitter in the brain and regulates other 
neurotransmissions to prevent overstimulation. Glycine is one of three amino acids 
needed for the synthesis of creatine, which supplies energy to nerve and muscle 
cells. It is the primary amino acid that regulates neurotransmission in the brain and 
spinal cord. A perennial botanical, Dong quai, is effective in easing post-exercise 
muscle soreness, and has long been used medicinally for smooth muscle tension. 
Vitamin B6 is required to convert glutamic acid to GABA. The vitamin is also a 
cofactor in many cellular biochemical reactions, including the release of glucose 
from glycogen. Magnesium, the fourth-most abundant mineral in the body, 
participates in approximately 300-350 enzymatic reactions within the body. It 
also plays an important role in regulating the influx of calcium into muscle cells to 
promote muscle relaxation and decrease muscle spasm.
 GABAnol is a synergistic combination of gamma-aminobutyric acid (GABA), 
glycine and Dong quai, which serves as a quick response supplement for 
muscle relaxation.

Description:
Glucosamine sulfate has a long history and 
extensive body of research highlighting its role in 
protecting cartilage, the shock-absorbing gel-like 
matter located between joints in the body.
Contents:
As the key precursor to cartilage formation, glucosamine sulfate supports connective tissue health to provide full support for joint comfort, as well as integrity 
and movement, while maintaining normal inflammatory balance. Glucosamine 
sulfate is also a precursor to chondroitin sulfate and hyaluronic acid, both 
of which are natural compounds found in the synovial fluid of cartilage. This 
glucosamine sulfate formulation is a high-purity product, and includes 750 mg of 
glucosamine sulfate per capsule for maximum care in joint health.

Description: GlutaShield® is designed to promote the health and barrier function of the gastrointestinal lining
Contents:
GlutaShield® includes nutrients to support the gut mucosal epithelium, which allows 
the digestion and absorption of dietary nutrients and keeps unwanted toxins, microbes 
and food particles from passing directly into the body. GlutaShield® includes a high
dose of L-glutamine, an amino acid that has been shown to enhance the normal 
repair and regeneration of the mucosal lining and provide energy for muscle repair and 
growth. It provides deglycyrrhized licorice root extract (DGL) to help maintain the 
mucosal surface, and aloe vera leaf gel extract to promote a normal inflammatory 
response. N-acetyl D-glucosamine, a mucin precursor, has been shown to increase 
the production of mucus in the gastrointestinal tract. Zinc, another ingredient widely 
recognized for its role in gut health, helps strengthen tight junctions in the GI barrier.

Description: GlycemaCORE is designed to help promote healthy blood sugar levels
Contents:
With its high fiber (13 g) content from inulin and Sunfiber®, and 10 g of protein from rice, GlycemaCORE helps maintain blood 
sugar balance after a meal, leading to less fatigue. GlycemaCORE provides 1.3 g of omega-3 fatty acids from flaxseeds and 
has no added sugar. Alpha lipoic acid is added for its powerful antioxidant support, insulin regulation and AMPK signaling to 
support optimal glucose disposal and weight management. Chromium is also included to support glucose tolerance factor 
(GTF) production, critical for cellular uptake of glucose. Vanadyl sulfate is another key nutrient included to promote blood 
sugar regulation and increase insulin sensitivity. GlycemaCORE is available in delicious rich chocolate and creamy vanilla flavors.

Description:
HepatoCORE is a blend of bergamot, artichoke and aged black garlic to 
support normal liver fat and lipid levels, promote weight management, and 
support vascular health.
Contents:
Maintaining normal liver fat levels is a growing concern in those with cardiovascular 
and liver challenges. HepatoCORE contains a clinically proven blend of bergamot and 
artichoke extracts along with aged black garlic extract to support normal liver and 
vascular function. In addition, it promotes normal metabolism and weight management 
to optimize cardiovascular wellness.

Description:
HiPhenolic is a high-concentration, highly purified polyphenolic blend that 
has been scientifically demonstrated to make positive shifts in functional 
metabolic targets. It provides multidimensional support to maintain blood 
pressure levels already within the normal range, manage weight, and increase 
satiety and appetite control.
Contents:
Longstanding evidence demonstrates that polyphenol-rich foods support normal 
metabolic and cardiovascular function. More recently, targeted, high-concentration 
polyphenols have been shown to act synergistically on functional metabolic and 
cardiovascular endpoints. HiPhenolic is a science-based blend of hibiscus, lemon 
verbena and green coffee bean extract that has been shown to support 
normal blood pressure levels and activate key metabolic pathways that increase 
thermogenesis, support healthy weight, and significantly increase satiety and  
reduce cravings.

Description:
Hormone Foundation is an innovative formula combining the synergistic 
benefits of Fermented CoreBiome® (tributyrin), TrueBroc® (glucoraphanin), 
EGCG, Complete Turmeric Matrix, Quatrefolic® (methylfolate), and Hops 
extract. These ingredients promote healthy estrogen production, optimize 
hormone detoxification, and increase free radical protection to harmonize all 
hormone protocols.
Contents:
Supporting healthy estrogen metabolism is essential for hormone balance and
 helps reduce the buildup of potentially harmful estrogen metabolites. This product
 is designed to enhance estrogen processing and elimination while providing
 antioxidant support to maintain cellular health and maintain normal inflammatory
 balance. Fermented CoreBiome® (tributyrin) is a short-chain fatty acid that
 promotes a healthy gut environment by supporting the gut lining and microbiome
 diversity. Tributyrin enhances gut-derived estrogen detoxification by nourishing
 beneficial bacteria involved in the elimination of estrogen metabolites. Derived from
 broccoli seed extract, glucoraphanin (TrueBroc®) is a precursor to sulforaphane,
 a potent compound that promotes liver enzyme activity essential for estrogen
 detoxification. Sulforaphane supports Phase II liver detoxification, aiding in the
 breakdown and removal of excess estrogens. The active compound in green tea,
 EGCG, provides antioxidant support and helps balance estrogen metabolism.
 Complete Turmeric Matrix delivers curcuminoids with enhanced bioavailability,
 supporting a balanced inflammatory response. Curcumin may also support liver
 function, which is crucial for the metabolism and excretion of
 estrogen and other hormones. A bioavailable form of folate,
 Quatrefolic® plays a role in methylation, a biochemical
 process essential for detoxification and hormone metabolism.
 Methylation helps reduce excess estrogen and promotes the
 production of beneficial estrogen metabolites. Hops supports
 estrogen metabolism through multiple pathways, including
 receptor modulation, aromatase inhibition, phytoestrogenic
 activity, and promoting liver health.

Nutrient_category: 1) IgG Protect Capsules2) IgG Protect Powder
Description:
IgG Protect is a highly concentrated (40%) immunoglobulin G (IgG) formula 
that provides essential nutrition for improved immune health.
Contents:
The immunoglobulins and growth factors in colostrum extract promote passive immunity, or the transfer of immunity from one organism to another. As the most 
abundant type of antibody, IgG, is primarily used to protect against unwanted organisms. Unlike standard colostrum products, which only offer 13-15% IgG, IgG Protect 
provides the purest, most potent concentration (40%) of IgG available. IgG Protect’s pure and high-concentration formula provides improved immune modulation and 
strengthens the gut-immune barrier. Consistency in potency and purity of colostrum extracts is a primary concern for clinicians. Advanced filtration and purification 
techniques make IgG Protect a superior clinical tool.
 Colostrum growth factors such as IGF-1, TGF-β2 and proline-rich peptides (PRPs) are necessary for stimulating normal epithelial tissue growth, in addition to upregulating 
B-cell growth and differentiation to increase antibody production by the body. PRPs have antioxidant properties that can address lipid peroxidation products which inhibit 
glutathione production. Lactoferrin is an iron-binding glycoprotein that facilitates iron absorption and protects against harmful organisms by depleting the environment of iron required for reproduction.
Benefits:
1)Maintain : Strengthen gut immune barrier 
while simultaneously improving 
nutrient absorption 2)Strengthen : Reduce antigen burden, 
strengthen mucosal barrier health 
and function, and help neutralize 
environmental toxins 3) Protect : Defend the gastrointestinal 
lining and maintain cytokine 
balance in the gut

Nutrient_category: Indigo Greens® Capsules Indigo Greens® Powder
Description:
Indigo Greens® provides FODMAP-friendly, certified all-organic nutrients 
following the USDA "My Plate" recommendations.
Contents:
The USDA's "MyPlate" program recommends that adult men and women load up 50% 
of their dinner plate with fruits and vegetables. Sadly, more than half of Americans are 
not consuming this amount on a daily basis. While most Americans know that fruits and 
vegetables are packed with nutrients, antioxidants and polyphenols that have been 
shown to have a positive impact on overall health, it can be difficult to comply with the 
current recommendations  with hectic schedules and modern conveniences such as fast 
food. Indigo Greens® provides a blend of organic fruits  and greens paired with a wide 
variety of organic vegetable powders to help bridge the gap in the typical American diet.  
Indigo Greens® can be taken as a standalone beverage mixed in juice or water, or used in 
a comprehensive fruit and vegetable smoothie to give an added boost of phytonutrients 
from organic fruits and vegetables. Children and adults alike are sure to enjoy and benefit 
from Indigo Greens® in their daily regime. Indigo Greens® is FODMAP-friendly and uses only 
certified organic fruits and vegetables.
Benefits:
1) Superfood Formulation :
 Packed with 16 superfoods to boost energy levels
 2) Full-Spectrum Nutrition :
 Concentrated, organic berries, vegetables and greens—
 a powerhouse of colorful nutrition 3) FODMAP-Friendly : 
 Supports a low-FODMAP diet for a healthy gut 
and reduced gas and bloating

Description:
Inflamma-bLOX is a comprehensive blend of 
phytonutrients providing full-spectrum, high
intensity support to maintain normal 
inflammatory balance
Contents:
Inflammation is a normal part of the body’s immune response, a cascade triggered 
to protect the body and maintain normal tissue repair. Inflamma-bLOX is designed 
to address immune challenges and support a healthy inflammatory cycle, helping to 
balance eicosanoid and cytokine metabolism and inhibit the activities and synthesis 
of a wide variety of compounds implicated in pain and inflammation from exercise. 
Inflamma-bLOX includes Complete Turmeric Matrix (CTM), which represents a 
new breakthrough in turmeric delivery. While most turmeric products focus merely 
on concentrating curcuminoids, CTM delivers an advanced, full-spectrum blend 
of additional bioactive turmeric phytonutrients shown to improve clinical efficacy. 
Studies have shown CTM supports healthy inflammation in the gastrointestinal 
tract. Skullcap root extract possesses potent antioxidant properties and research 
has shown it down-regulates NFkB activity and inhibits COX-2 expression. Propolis 
extract includes a diverse variety of potent terpenes, and benzoic, caffeic, cinnamic, 
and phenolic acids. It helps maintain a normal inflammatory response and protects 
against oxidative stress.
Formulated_For:
MUSCULOSKELETAL HEALTH
 GASTROINTESTINAL HEALTH
 MEN'S HEALTH

InosiCare is a cutting-edge inositol formula that includes clinically researched 
ingredients that harmonize metabolic function, optimize hormonal balance,

function and hormonal support. Together, these ingredients help promote energy

Contents: Ortho Biotic® and Ortho Biotic® 100 feature a diverse blend of proven strains shown to restore the natural microbiome and support immunity. In addition, BioShield® advanced encapsulation technology ensures live cultures are delivered intact and on target for maximum benefit. Each probiotic is formulated for maximum potency at room temperature storage

Description: Ortho Biotic® R is a unique reserve of probiotic strains for individuals who have an altered microbiome signature who need a targeted reset.
Contents: Ortho Biotic® R was developed for patients who have unique microbiome challenges that do not respond to typical probiotic regimens. These patients have been categorized as having a “resistor” type microbiome that needs to be reset and renewed. It upholds the same strain diversity and potency approach as Ortho Biotic® but contains a different set of seven probiotic strains including Saccharomyces boulardii, for enhanced gut microbial variety and ecosystem stability. In addition, it can be used for those who prefer a rotational approach to probiotics to bolster the microbiome footprint. Ortho Biotic® R offers an evidence-based, complementary probiotic formula to support individual microbiome needs.

Description: Ortho Biotic® Women's is formulated to maintain a healthy vaginal microbial balance
Contents: Every area of the human body has a unique ecology and therefore a unique microbiome. A healthy vaginal environment is mildly acidic, with Lactobacillus as the predominant species. To support pH balance and normal ecology, Ortho Biotic® Women's contains two specific species of Lactobacilli: reuteri and L. rhamnosus. These two species are common in a healthy vaginal ecosystem and the strains used are backed by human studies

Description: Ortho Digestzyme® is a full-spectrum enzyme strategically designed to support each phase of digestion.
Contents: In the gastric phase, betaine HCl and pepsin prime the stomach, ensuring proper pH to initiate the first phase of digestion. This sets up the second stage of digestion, the enteric phase, in which high-concentration pancreatin, which includes protease, amylase, and lipase, is released and activated in the small intestine to ensure proper protein breakdown and fat absorption. This unique blend of high-powered enzymes works in synergy to enhance digestion and ensure maximum nutrient absorption.

Description: Ortho Spore Complete is a unique spore-based, broad-spectrum probiotic formula designed to promote a healthy gut microbiota after SIBO.
Contents: Ortho Spore Complete is formulated with several spore-based probiotic strains to promote diversity and balance within the gut microbiota. Each capsule provides five key Bacillus strains that remain in a dormant, protective state in the harsh GI environment, then become active on target to transiently re-establish and recondition the gut to help prevent SIBO relapse.

Description: Ortho Spore IG® is a dual-action formulation, uniquely providing targeted, long-lasting effects of a spore-based probiotic with the binding capacity of serum-derived bovine immunoglobulins
Contents:
Ortho Spore IG® is a spore-based, broad-spectrum probiotic designed to promote a healthy gut microflora, protect mucosal integrity, and relieve small intestinal bacterial overgrowth (SIBO). Each capsule of Ortho Spore IG® provides key Bacillus spore-forming probiotic strains that remain in a dormant protective state in the harsh gastrointestinal environment and become active on target to colonize and recondition the gut. In addition, high-concentration, dairy-free immunoglobulins bind and eliminate microbial components and toxins commonly found in SIBO.Quorum Sensing
  Bacillus species use quorum sensing to group together, communicate, and produce active compounds that deter unwanted organisms. This intelligent networking triggers the production of 
 key enzymes that inhibit the growth of undesirable bacteria.
  Immunoglobulin Protection
  The result of Bacillus species inhibiting the growth of undesirable bacteria is ultimately bacterial breakdown, which can expose the gut to toxic compounds. That is why it is important to use 
 concentrated immunoglobulins, which have broad-spectrum capacity to bind toxins and cell components released when bacteria are broken down. This neutralizes and protects the GI tract 
 while supporting healthy microbial balance

Contents: Orthomega® 820 is a high-concentration fish oil sourced from waters off the Chilean coast. As the world’s least-industrialized coastline, these cold, fresh waters provide the cleanest, most sustainable source of fish in the world. Orthomega® provides 820 mg of eicosapentaenoic acid (EPA) and docosahexaenoic acid (DHA) per soft gel as triglycerides, the preferred form with superior absorption. The human body is accustomed to digesting and absorbing EPA and DHA in the triglyceride form. Despite this, the majority of fish oil products available on the market are in the ethyl ester form. The unusual structure of ethyl esters is resistant to the digestive enzymes that enable fat breakdown. The triglyceride form found in Orthomega® 820 allows for enhanced absorption and better assimilation in the body. To stabilize the oil, vitamin E (as mixed tocopherols) and rosemary extract are used to ensure maximum purity and freshness. This exclusive fish oil is purified, vacuum-distilled and independently tested to ensure heavy metals, pesticides and polychlorinated biphenyls (PCBs) are removed to undetectable levels. While most of the studies over the past three decades have focused on EPA and DHA, in recent years, there has been a growing interest in the omega-3 intermediate compound docosapentaenoic acid (DPA). Research has shown DPA collects in a variety of tissues, including the liver, breasts, brain, eyes, heart and red blood cells. DPA is the intermediate from EPA to DHA, and combined with the retroconversion of DHA to EPA, is now being considered an important reservoir for both EPA and DHA. Based on this growing body of research, each Orthomega® 820 soft gel contains 50 mg of DPA
Formulated_For:
ESSENTIAL FATTY ACIDS, CARDIOVASCULAR HEALTH
  MUSCULOSKELETAL HEALTH

The triglyceride form found in Orthomega® Liquid allows for enhanced absorption and better assimilation in the body. The Orthomega® Liquid formulation is a convenient method of achieving optimal omega-3 levels in the body. The natural mango-flavored liquid is the ideal alternative to encapsulated fish oil supplements.

It is sourced from waters off the Chilean coast, where cold, fresh waters provide the cleanest, most sustainable source of fish in the world. Orthomega® Select DHA delivers 580 mg of DHA per soft gel in the triglyceride form for superior absorption. This high-concentration DHA fish oil is purified, vacuum-distilled and independently tested to ensure heavy metals, pesticides and polychlorinated biphenyls (PCBs) are removed to undetectable levels. Description: OrthoMune® combines the power of quercetin and vitamin C to support immune function in all patients including pregnant, breastfeeding, and those with autoimmunity.
Contents: OrthoMune® is a targeted blend of nutrients designed to provide broad-spectrum support to the body’s immune reserves. The formula includes quercetin, a powerful bioflavonoid that aids in supporting the immune system. Vitamin C and N-acetyl cysteine are potent antioxidants that promote respiratory function and support the function of quercetin. Vitamin D and zinc are important micronutrients needed to create a robust immune reserve. This powerful combination works to promote healthy respiratory and immune function

Description: OsteoBase provides targeted doses of magnesium, vitamin K, vitamin D, and calcium critical to maintaining foundational bone health.
Contents: Conclusive research has shown bone tissue requires key nutrients to establish peak bone mass and maintain healthy bone density. OsteoBase provides 300 mg of calcium (150 mg in the form of hydroxyapatite) and 300 mg of magnesium per serving, in a 1:1 ratio. Calcium is most well-known for its role in the formation of bone and teeth, but it also plays a role in keeping the heart and muscles functioning by governing muscle contractions. Research indicates that up to 50% of the population is deficient in magnesium. Magnesium is also a constituent of bone and controls potassium and calcium uptake, assists in electrical nerve activity, and manages the metabolism of carbohydrates. Magnesium is required to activate vitamin D, and plays a key role in the architecture and strength of the hydroxyapatite crystals in bone's matrix. Magnesium enhances the absorption of calcium, and works in tandem with calcium to allow muscles to contract and relax. Combined, these two essential minerals maintain an intricately linked relationship that supports both muscle and nervous system function. Vitamin K2 (MK-7) as MenaQ7®PRO helps to bind newly absorbed calcium to the mineral matrix in bone through its activation of the protein osteocalcin. In addition, vitamin K has been found to help maintain bone mineral density by decreasing the activity of osteoclasts, or cells that break down the bone matrix. In this way, vitamin K and vitamin D not only share similar qualities, but also act in synergy within the body. This formulation includes 45 mcg of vitamin K2 and 25mcg (1,000 IU) of vitamin D3 per serving, for optimal absorption and use by the body.

Description: OsteoPrev is a formulation specifically designed to help maintain and support healthy bone mineral density.
Contents: OsteoPrev includes Albion® chelated minerals for enhanced bioavailability of calcium, magnesium, copper, manganese and molybdenum. OsteoPrev also includes vitamins D and K and phytonutrients to help support bone health and maintenance. Bone mineral density (BMD) is a major determinant of bone mass and is the most common measurement of the quality of bone. Consuming a healthy diet and ensuring optimal levels of bone-building vitamins and minerals are key strategies for preserving bone strength. BMD is determined by a lifelong process called bone remodeling. Bone remodeling occurs when bone tissue is removed from the skeleton (bone reabsorption) and new bone tissue is formed. While calcium is an effective starting point for promoting bone health, other nutrients are required for bone mineralization. Nutrients, such as magnesium, boron, vitamin K and D and trace minerals, significantly enhance the bone mineralization process. OsteoPrev provides full-spectrum nutrition to optimize the bone mineralization process and help maintain bone mineral density.

Description: Formulated with the goal of supporting microbial balance in the gastrointestinal tract, Paracid Forte includes potent botanicals to provide microbial balance.
Contents:
The body’s immune system is a complex and dynamic defense system, and healthy 
 microbial balance and antioxidant support help ensure optimal immune function. 
 Maintaining healthy microbial balance is not only integral to optimal GI health, but 
 also in supporting overall health and wellbeing. Paracid Forte provides a blend 
 of plant compounds that work together to defend against microbial stressors. 
 Wormwood is a fern-like plant commonly found throughout Asia. Artemisinin, 
 the active constituent of Artemisia annua, is a sesquiterpene lactone, a special 
 compound shown to have strong microbial-balancing properties. It is known to 
 interfere with microbial metabolism by causing structural changes to unfriendly 
 organisms that prevent them from maturing in the body. The active constituent of 
 olive leaf extract, oleuropein, is a unique polyphenol molecule with 
 microbial-balancing and antioxidant properties. The hulls of the black walnut 
 have been used since Greek and Roman times to support those with GI complaints. 
 Black walnut has tannins, compounds which affect the structural stability of various 
 microbes. These ingredients help maintain a healthy GI environment by supplying 
 compounds shown to create a hostile environment for various microbes

Description: The Phosphatidylserine formula provides 100 mg of purified, high concentration phosphatidylserine per serving, sourced from sunflower oil.
Contents: Phosphatidylserine is a fat-soluble phospholipid used to support optimal endocrine and cognitive health. Together with other phospholipids, phosphatidylserine is an integral component of the basic structure of the cell membrane. It plays a critical role in ensuring proper function of numerous systems in the body, especially the central nervous system. Studies using phosphatidylserine highlight its benefits for brain and cognitive health. It has been shown to enhance memory, learning and concentration. In addition, it has been shown to decrease cortisol release in response to stress by blunting the signaling of adrenocorticotropic hormone within the hypothalamic-pituitary-adrenal (HPA) axis. Since very little phosphatidylserine is found in food, this nutrient can be supplemented to provide support for optimal brain and endocrine health and stress resililence

Description: Phytocidal is a blend of powerful botanicals used to support the immune system when considering spirochetes.
Contents: Phytocidal provides a blend of potent botanicals to promote healthy microbial balance and immune support. Formulated with the goal of reducing immune burden, Phytocidal includes cat’s claw, an herb that suppresses TNF-alpha synthesis and can raise CD57 counts in patients with a high spirochete load. In addition, Japanese knotweed supports vessel health and balances cytokines. Andrographis supports inflammatory balance and contributes to microbial balance. Artemisinin is a sesquiterpene lactone, a special compound shown to have strong microbial-balancing properties. It is known to interfere with microbial metabolism by causing structural changes to unfriendly organisms that prevent them from maturing in the body. This effect is facilitated by the production of free radicals and reactive aldehydes within the microbes that disrupt their growth.

Description: PhytoCore was created as a component of the Core Restore® program. The specialized blend of nutrients in PhytoCore has been shown to stimulate Phase I and II biotransformation and support the body’s natural liver cleansing function during detoxification.
Contents: Each capsule of PhytoCore includes milk thistle seed (silymarin), artichoke extract, curcumin, methionine, choline, inositol, garlic, and dandelion root. It includes Complete Turmeric Matrix (CTM), which represents a new breakthrough in turmeric delivery. While most turmeric products focus merely on concentrating curcuminoids, CTM delivers an advanced, full-spectrum blend of additional bioactive turmeric phytonutrients shown to improve clinical efficacy. These botanicals and plant extracts have phytonutrients, antioxidants and other compounds shown to increase cellular defenses, up-regulate detoxification, and protect DNA.

Description: PhytoPre® is a unique blend of bioactive compounds from citrus bioflavonoids and pomegranate extract proven to recondition the gut and increase microbial diversity without the uncomfortable side effects often seen in fiber-based prebiotics.
Contents:
When it comes to the most sensitive patients with SIBO or multiple symptoms of 
 GI discomfort, it is important to choose a proven prebiotic solution that is gentle, 
 welell-tolerated and effective. Traditional fiber-based prebiotics are certainly not appropriate for everyone and can potentially worsen symptoms due to rapid fermentation that can cause gas, bloating, diarrhea, or constipation in sensitive patients. PhytoPre® is a non-fiber prebiotic containing a unique blend of citrus bioflavonoids (MicrobiomeX®) and concentrated pomegranate extract (Pomanox®). Multiple clinical studies have demonstrated their ability to recondition the gut microflora without the side-effects often seen with fiber-based prebiotics. This targeted combination has been shown to increase healthy keystone strains of Lactobacillus and Bifidobacterium and increase the production of butyrate, a critical short-chain fatty acid that nourishes and promotes a healthy GI barrier. In addition, a 12-week randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled study demonstrated that 500 mg of citrus bioflavonoids (MicrobiomeX®) lowered calprotectin levels, a key marker of normal inflammatory balance in the GI tract.

Description: Research has shown that phytosterols, or plant-based compounds structurally similar to cholesterol, compete with cholesterol for absorption and thus play a key role in supporting healthy cholesterol levels already within the normal range.
Contents: According to the Food and Drug Administration, “products containing at least 0.65 g per serving of plant sterol esters, taken twice daily with meals for a daily total intake of at least 1.3 g, as part of a diet low in saturated fat and cholesterol, may reduce the risk of heart disease.” The National Cholesterol Education Program (NCEP) of the National Heart, Lung and Blood Institute of Health suggests the use of plant sterols to promote cardiovascular health. The Plant Sterols complex includes a variety of purified plant sterols, including campestrol, stigmasterol, B-sitosterol and other cholesterol-like compounds. Phytosterols undergo absorption similar to that of cholesterol. Both must be incorporated into mixed micelles before being taken up by enterocytes in the intestinal lining. During this process, phytosterols displace cholesterol from food and reduce cholesterol absorption, resulting in a beneficial effect on blood cholesterol levels.

Description:
Pregnenolone plays a key role in hormonal balance as a key precursor to 
 cortisol, dehydroepiandrosterone (DHEA) and progesterone, and helps to 
 maintain balance in the body’s stress response system
Contents:
Pregnenolone has been shown to support a balanced mood and promote 
 cognitive health by modulating the transmission of messages between neurons, 
 influencing learning and memory processes. As a biochemical precursor to DHEA 
 and progesterone, pregnenolone helps to keep a normal balance between these 
 hormones in the body and modulate the cortisol-driven stress response system. 
 There is strong evidence that pregnenolone levels diminish with age, and restoring 
 these levels may elevate overall brain function, mood and sense of wellbeing. Each 
 tablet of this Pregnenolone formulation provides 10 mg of pregnenolone in a 
 scored, quick-dissolve tablet, allowing for incremental dosing as needed.

Description: Pro Bono® is the most advanced bone-building protocol specifically designed to increase skeletal strength and help maintain and support healthy bone density.
Contents: Pro Bono® provides therapeutic doses of clinically proven, bone-stimulating nutrients in convenient, easy-to-take packets to enhance bone formation. The foundation of Pro Bono® is 1,000 mg of strontium citrate, a well-researched bone-supporting mineral proven to strengthen the bone matrix and support skeletal density. Strontium is a mineral similar to the physical and chemical properties of calcium. Research has shown strontium to provide natural bone support through its ability to increase the formation of osteoblasts while decreasing the formation of osteoclasts. Strontium also provides an anabolic effect on bone by stimulating bone morphogenic proteins and enhancing calcium deposition and mineralization in the bone matrix. Each serving provides the most bioavailable sources of strontium, calcium, magnesium, vitamin D3 and K2 (MK-7) as MenaQ7®PRO, boron and other trace minerals to support bone health. Pro Bono® also includes a full complement of micronutrients, making an additional multivitamin unnecessary.

Description: prostatrol Forte includes botanicals and trace minerals that work in synergy to promote prostate health.
Contents: The formula includes a potent, standardized extract of saw palmetto, an extract of stinging nettles root and a standardized extract of pygeum bark. It also includes the chelated form of zinc, copper and selenium to support healthy prostate function. Compromised prostate function can affect several factors of men’s health, including urinary flow. The combination of increased estrogen levels and elevated dihydrotestosterone (DHT) is thought to be a key factor. Natural botanicals that prevent increased DHT and estrogen levels are included in Prostatrol Forte to promote healthy urinary flow, hormone metabolism and overall prostate health.

Description: Reacted Calcium provides three unique forms of highly-absorbed calcium to ensure maximum absorption of this important macromineral
Contents: While most calcium supplements use only a single source of calcium, which can easily overwhelm a single pathway of absorption and limit uptake, Reacted Calcium takes advantage of three unique pathways of absorption by providing calcium in the hydroxyapatite, di-calcium malate, and glycinate forms. In addition, Reacted Calcium includes vitamin D and phosphorus, both critical nutrients for bone mineralization and remodeling.

Description: While most mineral supplements use only a single-source of minerals which can easily overwhelm a single pathway of absorption and limit the uptake of high-dose calcium-magnesium regimens, Reacted Cal-Mag leverages the benefit of multiple pathways of absorption by using three different mineral forms.
Contents: Calcium is most well-known for its role in the formation of bone and teeth, but it also plays a role in keeping the heart and muscles functioning by governing muscle contractions. Magnesium is also a constituent of bone and controls potassium and calcium uptake, assists in electrical nerve activity, and manages the metabolism of carbohydrates. In the body, phosphorus is second in abundance only to calcium, and is necessary for bone growth, cellular health and acid-alkaline balance. Magnesium enhances the absorption of calcium, and works in tandem with calcium to allow muscles to contract and relax.
